<p>A crime has been committed, and it is known that the criminal is part is part of a population of 6 million. Through research, the police know that only one person per million has DNA that matches the DNA of the perpetrator. Define the events:‖<br />
* <em>A</em> = the DNA of a randomly selected person matches the DNA of the offender.
* <em>B</em> = the person chosen is innocent.  Then what is the probability that the police will choose a person who is innocent, given that his DNA matches that of the perpetrator?</p>
</p>]]></text>
